        <h2>1. Buildertrend — Best scheduling for residential builders</h2>
        <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Essential $499/mo · Advanced $799/mo · Complete $1,099/mo</p>

        <p>Buildertrend's scheduling module is the gold standard for residential construction. The Gantt chart interface supports task dependencies, which means when one task slips, the system cascades that delay through all dependent tasks automatically. Your schedule stays accurate without manually moving everything.</p>

        <p><strong>Scheduling-specific strengths:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Dependency tracking:</strong> Link tasks so delays automatically propagate downstream</li>
          <li><strong>Sub notifications:</strong> Subs receive automated reminders when their work window approaches</li>
          <li><strong>Weather integration:</strong> Flag weather-related delays directly in the schedule</li>
          <li><strong>Client visibility:</strong> Homeowners can view the schedule in real-time through the client portal</li>
          <li><strong>Template schedules:</strong> Build master schedules and apply them to new projects in minutes</li>
          <li><strong>Multi-project view:</strong> See all your jobs on one calendar — critical for managing overlapping builds</li>
        </ul>

        <p><strong>Limitations:</strong></p>
        <ul>
          <li>$499/mo is expensive if scheduling is your only need</li>
          <li>Scheduling is part of the full platform — you can't purchase just this module</li>
          <li>Critical path management not as sophisticated as enterprise tools like Primavera P6</li>
        </ul>

